b'tlowery1'
b'Office of Student Affairs'
b'The mission of the Office of Student Affairs\xc2\xa0at the College of Medicine Rockford is to help students succeed in attaining their academic, career and personal goals. We achieve this mission by striving to provide exemplary student services, resources, guidance and advocacy while addressing students\xe2\x80\x99 diverse backgrounds and needs. In partnership with undergraduate medical education leaders and others, we help create a supportive, welcoming, nurturing, enriching, challenging and inclusive environment in which students are empowered to express their perspectives.'
b'Our dedicated staff in the Office of Student Affairs provides resources and information to help students succeed, including information about housing, academic support services, career development, community service activities, licensure exams and resources, and residency applications and matching.'
b'The\xc2\xa0Office of Student Affairs\xc2\xa0in Rockford facilitates a wide range of co-curricular support services for students including:'
b'Financial aid'
b'CampusCare'
b'Students are encouraged to contact the Assistant Dean for Student Affairs with any questions or concerns.'
b'Assistant Dean for Student Affairs'
